\section{Conclusion}


\begin{frame}

\begin{exampleblock}{Conclusions:}
\begin{itemize}
\item We proposed temporal-mode interferometry (TMI) for wave-packet multiplexing and demultiplexing\footnotemark[5].
\begin{itemize}
\item Clemmen et al (CLEO:2014: FTh5A.2) have since experimentally demonstrated `color-qubit' with CW pumps, {\it i.e.} with no selectivity.
\end{itemize}
\item TMI, together with existing methods, enables all linear quantum operations on single-photon wave-packets.
\item TMI enables multidimensional and continuous wave operations on the same.
\end{itemize}
\end{exampleblock}
